25|$|In medium-power {{transmission}} applications, {{even more}} complex and sophisticated voltage sourced converter (VSC) silicon semiconductor rectifier systems, such as insulated gate <b>bipolar</b> <b>transistors</b> (IGBT) and gate turn-off thyristors (GTO), have made smaller high voltage DC power transmission systems economical. All of these devices function as rectifiers.|$|E
