25|$|Most <b>bipolar</b> <b>transistors,</b> and {{especially}} power transistors, have long base-storage {{times when they}} are driven into saturation; the base storage limits turn-off time in switching applications. A Baker clamp can prevent the transistor from heavily saturating, which reduces the amount of charge stored in the base, and thus improves switching time.|$|E
